column1: #Text=# OpenSTL: A Comprehensive Benchmark of Spatio-Temporal Predictive Learning

#Text=OpenSTL is a comprehensive benchmark for spatio-temporal predictive learning, encompassing a broad spectrum of methods and diverse tasks, ranging from synthetic moving object trajectories to real-world scenarios such as human motion, driving scenes, traffic flow, and weather forecasting.
#Text=  OpenSTL decomposes STL algorithms into `methods` (training and prediction), `models` (network architectures), and `modules`, while providing unified experiment API.
#Text=Users can develop their own STL algorithms with flexible training strategies and networks for different STL tasks

#Text=  OpenSTL will support standard benchmarks of STL algorithms image with training and evaluation as many open-source projects (e.g., [MMDetection](https://github.com/open-mmlab/mmdetection) and [USB](https://github.com/microsoft/Semi-supervised-learning)).
#Text=We are working on training benchmarks and will update results synchronizingly

#Text=  We plan to provide benchmarks of various STL methods and MetaFormer architectures based on SimVP in various STL application tasks, e.g., video prediction, weather prediction, traffic prediction, etc.
#Text=We encourage researchers interested in STL to contribute to OpenSTL or provide valuable advice!
#Text=- `openstl/core` contains core training plugins and metrics.
#Text=- `openstl/methods/` contains training methods for various video prediction methods.
#Text=- `openstl/models/` contains the main network architectures of various video prediction methods.
#Text=- `tools/` contains the executable python files `tools/train.py` and `tools/test.py` with possible arguments for training, validating, and testing pipelines.
#Text=[2023-09-23] The OpenSTL paper has been accepted by NeurIPS 2023 Dataset and Benchmark Track!
#Text=[2023-06-19] `OpenSTL` v0.3.0 is released and will be enhanced in [#25](https://github.com/chengtan9907/OpenSTL/issues/25).

#Text=Here is an example of single GPU non-distributed training SimVP+gSTA on Moving MNIST dataset.
#Text=For the convenience of users, we provide a tutorial on how to train, evaluate, and visualize with OpenSTL on custom data.
#Text=This tutorial enables users to quickly build their own projects using OpenSTL.
#Text=For more details, please refer to the [`tutorial.ipynb`](examples/tutorial.ipynb) in the `examples/` directory.
#Text=We also provide a Colab demo of this tutorial:
#Text=## Overview of Model Zoo and Datasets
#Text=We support various spatiotemporal prediction methods and provide [benchmarks](https://github.com/chengtan9907/OpenSTL/tree/master/docs/en/model_zoos) on various STL datasets.
#Text=We present visualization examples of ConvLSTM below.
#Text=For more detailed information, please refer to the [visualization](docs/en/visualization/)

#Text=- For synthetic moving object trajectory prediction and real-world video prediction, visualization examples of other approaches can be found in [visualization/video_visualization.md](docs/en/visualization/video_visualization.md).
#Text=BAIR and Kinetics are not benchmarked and only for illustration
#Text=- For traffic flow prediction, visualization examples of other approaches are shown in [visualization/traffic_visualization.md](docs/en/visualization/traffic_visualization.md)
#Text=- For weather forecasting, visualization examples of other approaches are shown in [visualization/weather_visualization.md](docs/en/visualization/weather_visualization.md).

#Text=This project is released under the [Apache 2.0 license](LICENSE).
#Text=OpenSTL is an open-source project for STL algorithms created by researchers in **CAIRI AI Lab**.
#Text=We encourage researchers interested in video and weather prediction to contribute to OpenSTL!

#Text=We borrow the official implementations of [ConvLSTM](https://arxiv.org/abs/1506.04214), [PredNet](https://arxiv.org/abs/1605.08104), [PredRNN](https://dl.acm.org/doi/abs/10.5555/3294771.3294855) variants, [E3D-LSTM](https://openreview.net/forum?

#Text=For adding new features, looking for helps, or reporting bugs associated with `OpenSTL`, please open a [GitHub issue](https://github.com/chengtan9907/OpenSTL/issues) and [pull request](https://github.com/chengtan9907/OpenSTL/pulls) with the tag "new features", "help wanted", or "enhancement".
